request.description:
## Bulk Update — Full Replace Multiple Records

Replace multiple records entirely. Each item needs `id` (primary key) and `data` (the complete replacement object).

### Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `master` | String | **Yes** | Master/entity name |
| `input.data` | String | **Yes** | JSON string of array of `{ id, data }` objects |

### Data Format

```json
[
  {
    "id": "1",
    "data": {
      "master_id": "1",
      "sku": "BLK-SKU-001",
      "name": "Bulk Updated 1",
      "price": "999",
      "category": "Updated"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "2",
    "data": {
      "master_id": "2",
      "sku": "BLK-SKU-002",
      "name": "Bulk Updated 2",
      "price": "888",
      "category": "Updated"
    }
  }
]
```

### Important

- This is a **full replace** — each `data` object must contain ALL fields
- Any field missing from `data` will be removed from the record
- Use **Bulk Patch** instead if you only want to change specific fields
- Records not found are reported as individual failures

### Example Response

```json
{
  "data": {
    "mdmBulkUpdate": {
      "master": "productcatalog",
      "operation": "bulkUpdate",
      "total": 2,
      "succeeded": 2,
      "failed": 0,
      "results": [
        { "success": true, "id": "1", "error": null },
        { "success": true, "id": "2", "error": null }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

